text: Arnaldo Horacio Arocha Vargas (10 September 1936 â€“ 8 February 2022) was a Venezuelan politician. He was a member of Copei. He was Governor of Miranda from 1971 to 1974 and again from 1990 to 1995. He also was in the Venezuelan Chamber of Deputies from 1969 to 1974 and again from 1984 to 1989. Arocha was born in Charallave, Venezuela. Arocha died on 8 February 2022, at the age of 85. ==References== Category:1936 births Category:2022 deaths Category:Venezuelan politicians
